{"readme":"<h1 class=\"title\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/mikolalysenko/affine-hull\">affine-hull</a><div class=\"contrib\"></div></h1>\n<p>Computes the lexicographically smallest basis for the affine hull of a point set.</p>\n<h2 id=\"example\">Example</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-javascript\"><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>var&#xA0;aff&#xA0;=&#xA0;require(&apos;affine-hull&apos;)</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>&#xA0;</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>console.log(aff([</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;[0,&#xA0;0,&#xA0;0],</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;[1,&#xA0;0,&#xA0;0],</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;[2,&#xA0;0,&#xA0;0],</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;[3,&#xA0;0,&#xA0;0],</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;[0,&#xA0;1,&#xA0;0],</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>&#xA0;&#xA0;[0,&#xA0;0,&#xA0;2]</span></span></div><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>]))</span></span></div>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-javascript\"><div class=\"line\"><span class=\"source js\"><span>[0,&#xA0;1,&#xA0;4,&#xA0;5]</span></span></div>\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"install\">Install</h2>\n<pre><code>npm install affine-hull\n</code></pre><h2 id=\"api\">API</h2>\n<h4 id=\"require-affine-hull-points-\"><code>require(&apos;affine-hull&apos;)(points)</code></h4>\n<p>Computes a basis for the affine hull of the set of points <code>points</code>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>points</code> is a list of points encoded by d-tuples of numbers</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Returns</strong> A list of indices for the generators of the affine hull of the point set</p>\n<h2 id=\"credits\">Credits</h2>\n<p>(c) 2014 Mikola Lysenko. MIT License</p>\n"}